1
00:00:00,166 --> 00:00:02,500
They brought two
meals, morning and noon

2
00:00:03,833 --> 00:00:05,541
They would bring rice
and broth, that was at noon

3
00:00:07,000 --> 00:00:08,583
And in the morning they
gave you a <i>samoon</i> [bread roll]

4
00:00:09,583 --> 00:00:11,500
Or a biscuit or some dates

5
00:00:12,625 --> 00:00:13,708
That's what they gave

6
00:00:13,750 --> 00:00:16,666
Or biscuit with dates

7
00:00:17,208 --> 00:00:19,125
Because most of them ate dates

8
00:00:19,833 --> 00:00:22,333
Dates with biscuit, or
dates with a <i>samoon</i>

9
00:00:23,375 --> 00:00:26,750
And at noon, rice

10
00:00:28,250 --> 00:00:31,041
They would bring it in large
dishes and everyone ate from them

11
00:00:33,833 --> 00:00:36,083
Interviewer: Was there a
race for the food, for example?

12
00:00:36,125 --> 00:00:39,833
To get your share from the big dish they
brought, or was there a portion for each person?

13
00:00:40,583 --> 00:00:44,666
No, no, each person got a
disposable plate just for him

14
00:00:47,416 --> 00:00:49,291
Interviewer: Was the
amount of food enough?

15
00:00:49,833 --> 00:00:53,375
There was no choice. I
spent only one night here

16
00:00:53,875 --> 00:00:56,916
And I ate one meal at noon
until the following morning

17
00:00:56,916 --> 00:00:58,958
So they brought
us biscuit and dates

18
00:00:59,916 --> 00:01:02,416
Of that small-sized biscuit

19
00:01:02,708 --> 00:01:05,291
And a little bit of dates
with it, and that's all

20
00:01:06,458 --> 00:01:07,791
After that I didn't
eat with them

21
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:13,458
Interviewer: So were
the meals regular?

22
00:01:13,458 --> 00:01:17,791
They would bring
it at one or 2 p.m.

23
00:01:18,208 --> 00:01:20,125
And they brought
breakfast to us at 9 a.m.

24
00:01:20,208 --> 00:01:22,083
Dates and biscuit

25
00:01:22,500 --> 00:01:24,041
I didn't eat anything else here

26
00:01:25,250 --> 00:01:27,375
Even at night there
was no dinner meal

27
00:01:27,958 --> 00:01:29,083
The last meal was lunch
